. What is Normalization?
Normalization is a feature scaling technique used during data preparation for machine learning. Its primary goal is to change the values of numerical columns to a common scale without distorting the differences in the ranges of values or losing information.
• Why it's used: Numerical quantities consist of magnitude and units (e.g., weight in kg or lbs). Machine learning algorithms often perform better when units are eliminated, and only the magnitudes are kept on a common scale.
• Geometric Intuition: It essentially "squeezes" or compresses your data into a unit rectangle (2D), unit cube (3D), or unit hypercube (higher dimensions).

