3. Practical Tips for Preparation
• Standardization vs. Normalization: Most machine learning problems are solved more effectively using Standardization, but Normalization is essential for specific scenarios like deep learning or image processing.
• Impact of Outliers: In Min-Max scaling, outliers can compress the "normal" data into a very small range, which is why Robust Scaling is preferred if outliers are present.
• Experimentation: Machine learning is about experimentation; it is often useful to try different scaling techniques to see which one yields the best performance for your specific dataset.
